Menard’s Sacramentary contains masses for all the days of this group: but its divergences frorn Mur. are more consider· able. It may be observed that Gem. places before the mass of the Purification forms for the Benedictio Carnorum. These do not occur in Leofr. in the same position, or indeed at all in the earliest part of the text of the Leofric Missal: but the sarne prayers and anthems are provided in that portion of the text which Mr. Warreu distinguishes as C, that is to say, in the part of the Leofric Missal which appears to have been written in England, during the eleventh century!
